-- Fortress looks at bid for EMI: paper
-- 
-- Sun Feb 25, 2007 8:19am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/02/25/us-emi-fortress-idUSL2540001220070225

 

 LONDON  (Reuters) - U.S.-based Fortress Investment Group Llc ( FIG.N ) has joined the pack of potential bidders for British music firm EMI Group Plc EMI.L, The Sunday Telegraph reported, citing people familiar with the situation. 


 Fortress was undertaking detailed work on EMI ahead of an approach for the record label, the paper said. An EMI spokesman declined to comment, while no-one at Fortress was immediately available to comment. According to media reports, EMI is in talks with a number of private equity firms including One Equity Partners, a unit of JP Morgan Chase and Co. ( JPM.N ) over potential alternatives to a takeover approach from Warner Music Group WMG.N.